
"git init" - initializes the git repository
"git add ." -  adds the files to staging area
"git commit -m "first commit""  -  moves it to repository ?
"git remote add origin url" - connect the local repo with teh newly-created
    online one
"git remote -v" - shows the connections with outer repos
"git branch -M main" - MUST BE DONE!! - will be discussed later
    ot is for naming the branch and naming should be done
git push -u origin main - push the code to the remote repo for the first time





